<h3 id="hot-swappable-drive-cage-for-ssds"><a href="https://amzn.to/2QgAK9R" target="_blank">Hot Swappable Drive Cage for SSDs</a></h3>
<p><img class="img-right img-small lazyload" alt="4 hot swappable ssd drive cage" data-src="/img/cases/hot-swap/4-drive-ssds.jpg" /></p>

<p>The <a href="https://amzn.to/2QgAK9R" target="_blank">ICY DOCK Tough Armor Drive Bay</a> (model number MB882SP-1S-2B) is going to be your best bet if you want to hot swap 2.5‚Äù solid state drives.</p>

<p>This bad boy is nearly indestructible (the company ran it over with a car without causing any damage) and is pretty easy to use.</p>

<p>It mounts in a standard 5.25‚Äù bay which most <a href="/pc-cases/">PC cases</a> have these days, and can fit up to four hot swappable solid state drives.</p>

<p>Four drives in a single 5.25‚Äù drive bay isn‚Äôt too shabby, huh?</p>

<p>You can easily pop the drive bays out, screw your 2.5‚Äù SSD into the removable tray, and pop it into the drive bay.</p>

<p>In addition, this bad boy ships with its own set of daul 40mm cooling fans, which only activate when a drive is installed.</p>

<p>You should note, however, that the cooling fans do tend to run a bit loud, so you may want to invest in a soundproof case.</p>

<p>In addition, the SSDs performed nearly identical to their performance in a normal configuration, meaning performance isn‚Äôt lost when using this hot swappable drive bay.</p>

