<p>Simply screw it in to your 5.25‚Äù bay, pop your SSDs in there, and you‚Äôre good to go.</p>

<p>Once the 5.25‚Äù drive bay is mounted, you can connect your traditional SATA cables to the back.</p>

<p>All in all, this is a great option if you want to have a hot swappable 2.5‚Äù SATA SSD drive bay in your PC case without having to buy a NAS.</p>

