<h2 id="conclusion">Conclusion</h2>

<p>It‚Äôs almost impossible to find a regular PC case that supports hot swapping your drives.</p>

<p>If that‚Äôs what you‚Äôre looking for, buying a NAS case is probably a better option (we have a guide on NAS cases <a href="/pc-cases/nas/">here</a>.)</p>

<p>However, you can buy a hot swap cage and install it in your regular PC gaming case, which is probably the best option for traditional builders.</p>

<p>I hope this helps!</p>

